    h2 General terms
    p Welcome to the voji.co.uk website terms and conditions for use. These apply to the use of this Website and by accessing this Website and/or placing an order, you agree to be bound by the terms and conditions set out below. 
    p This site is owned and operated by Voji ,Registered office, 1st floor, Gallery Court , 28 Arcadia Avenue, London N3 2FG. Registered number 12602997 (England and Wales). Email us at contact@voji.co.uk
    p Voji Ltd is authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority in relation to credit broking. 
    h2 Amendments
    p We aim to constantly improve and develop the Voji website for the benefit of all our customers, to allow this process to take place, we may occasionally: 
    p Modify or withdraw, temporarily or permanently, this Website (or any part of it) with or without notice; and/or 
    p Change the Conditions from time to time, and your continued use of the Website (or any part of it) following such change will demonstrate your acceptance of such change.
    p Alter or extend promotions at any time. 
    p If Voji is informed of any inaccuracies in the material on the site we will attempt to correct them as soon as we reasonably can. 
    h2 Damage to your computer
    p Voji makes every effort to ensure that this website is free from viruses or defects. However, due to the nature of the Internet, we cannot guarantee that your use of this website won’t affect your computer. Voji recommends that you purchase the right firewall and antivirus software to use this and other websites and screen out anything that may damage it. Voji shall not be liable in the very unlikely event that while using this website your computer equipment is damaged. 
    h2 Accuracy of content
    p Voji has taken every care in the preparation of the content of this website, in particular to ensure that prices quoted are correct at time of publishing and all products have been fairly described. However, orders will only be accepted if there are no material errors in the description of the goods or their prices as advertised on this website. All prices are displayed inclusive of V.A.T. We make every effort to display the colour of the bikes as accurately as possible. But as colour reproduction depends on your computer’s monitor, we cannot guarantee that your monitor’s display of the colour is accurate to the actual product. 
    p Acknowledgement and acceptance of your order
    p Everything that Voji sells is typically built to order.. As a manufacturer we pride ourselves on being able to make products that's perfect for you. 
    p It is important that you appreciate and understand that this order is a legally binding contract. Your statutory rights, including any cancellation rights, are unaffected.
    h2 Processing your order and delivery dates
    p You will be informed of the likely approximate length of time until delivery after your order. Once your order is confirmed as available for delivery we will contact you to agree definite arrangements for the date of delivery. Where possible we will deliver on the first available van in your area.. Every effort is made to see that the approximate delivery date is accurate, but on rare occasions the manufacture of your bike may be delayed through circumstances beyond our control. We will, of course, make every effort to keep you informed. In the rare instance that a product line is unavailable we will replace it with a comparable product line of equal or better specification and in the same colour.
    p If you choose to pay by one of the interest free credit options the approximate delivery time will start once we have received your signed finance documents and sales contract.
    h2 Delivery and installation
    p A delivery charge of £150 (Ex. VAT) is made for the delivery of your bike within mainland UK  (Excluding the Highlands and Islands and Northern Ireland, Monday to Friday, If you wish your order to be delivered outside of mainland U.K we will be happy to provide you with a personal delivery quotation. 
    p EU Deliveries:
    p For all deliveries to other EU Member States excluding Ireland and the Netherlands, you will be required to enter into a separate contract with one of Voji’s trusted third party delivery providers for this delivery service. Voji will deliver your bike to the third party delivery provider's premises in the UK, at which point legal title in the bike will transfer to you. When you purchase your bike you also agree to enter into a separate contract with the appointed third party delivery provider who will deliver your bike from their UK premises to your chosen delivery address. The appointed delivery provider will make a charge to you for this delivery and installation service. For administrative ease, this payment will be collected by Voji and remitted to the third party delivery provider on your behalf.
    p Voji bikes come delivered in a protective box on a a pallet. It is not the delivery companies responsibility to remove the pallet. Please be aware that the front wheel of the bike is delivered in the box un-attached and requires simple attachment to the bike. In order to fit into the delivery box the handle bars are also twisted to the  side (as opposed to front facing) and require simple adjustment. Simple assembly instructions for the front wheel and adjustment of the handlebars are included and should take less than 5 minutes. We simply shop bikes in this fashion to reduce the cost of transport to you the end consumer.
    h2 Payment
    p Payment methods include debit or credit cards, Visa, Mastercard, Delta/Connect or Maestro and Klarna.
    h2 Outstanding balance
    p Before we deliver your products, you must have paid in full or have an Interest free credit repayment contract in place. Payment can not be taken on delivery.
    h2 Cancellation Policy
    p Consumer Contract regulations only apply to your order if the goods have not been custom made to your specification. If the Consumer Contract Regulations do apply you can cancel your bike by notifying us, in writing, before delivery or within 14 working days beginning with the day after the date of delivery.
    p Should you wish to return the goods it is your responsibility to take good care of the bike. You are the owner of the bike once it has been delivered to you and you are liable for any loss or damage. Failure to take reasonable care may result in a claim against you. To minimise the risk of any such claim we ask that you return the goods in appropriate packaging such as to prevent damage in transit.
    p If the bike has been ridden or damaged it will be deemed as used and a return or cancellation will not be possible. You will be subject to a fee of goods £895, plus a £500 cost for delivery and admin. Should you wish to return your goods it will be your responsibility to cover the costs of delivery.
    p If you would like to return the bike or cancel your order please email cancellations@voji.co.uk
    h2 Refunds
    p Following cancellation of your order any monies paid will be refunded by the method you used to pay us and usually within 14 days.
    p If you are unhappy with how your interest free credit was completed
    p Please contact our Customer Services Department by emailing contactus@voji.co.uk 
    p If we fail to resolve your interest free credit complaint you may be entitled to refer it to the Financial Ombudsman Service and their website address is www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk
    p Voji is authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority in relation to credit broking.
    h2 Your guarantee
    p Your bike will have a 2 year guarantee with the manufacturer. The bike batteries are guaranteed for a period of 6 months.
    p The guarantee starts from the date of delivery and offers cover against manufacturing defects. Additionally, motor mechanisms and electrical parts are covered for 2 years. 
    p There are some things that aren’t covered by your guarantee. For example, deliberate damage - like treating it roughly or not using the right products to maintain it. It also doesn’t cover your bike for use in a workplace or business..
    p And, don’t forget your 2 year guarantee only belongs to you. So if you sell or give away your bike, the guarantee ends.
    p As a consumer you have certain rights regarding defective goods and this guarantee is given in addition to and not in substitution of your statutory rights. This guarantee applies to mainland UK only.
